Interface GraphInterface

    • Method Detail

      • addNode

        void addNode​(int nodeToAdd)
        This will add an unconnected Node to the graph. It will have an empty Array List of Connections
        Parameters:
        nodeToAdd - - This is the node to add

      • addConnection

        void addConnection​(int originNode,
                   int destinationNode,
                   int weight)
        This will add a connection from the origin node to the destination node with the corresponding weight. If either node is not in graph it will be added to the graph
        Parameters:
        originNode - - The node to start the connection from
        destinationNode - - The node the connection goes to
        weight - - The weight of the node

      • removeNode

        void removeNode​(int nodeToRemove)
        This will remove the node from the graph and any connections to that node
        Parameters:
        nodeToRemove - - The node to remove from the graph

      • getConnections

        int[][] getConnections()
        This will get all the connections in the form of {originNode, destinationNode, weight}. This is then put in its own 2D array.
        Returns:
        2D array of all connections in the graph

      • removeConnection

        void removeConnection​(int originNode,
                      int destinationNode)
        This will remove the connection between the originNode and the destinationNode
        Parameters:
        originNode - - The originNode of the connection to remove
        destinationNode - - The destinationNode of the connection to remove

      • getNumberOfNodes

        int getNumberOfNodes()
        This will get the number of nodes which are in the graph - Like .size()
        Returns:
        - The number of nodes in the graph as an integer

      • getConnection

        java.util.ArrayList<Connection> getConnection​(int nodeNum)
        This will get all the connections fir that node
        Parameters:
        nodeNum - - The node to get the connections for
        Returns:
        An ArrayList of Connections of the connections for that node
